programme.desc: Proof that music can change lives can be found with the Fundación del Estado para el Sistema Nacional de las Orquestas Juveniles e Infantiles de Venezuela. This network of about 125 youth orchestras enables children from the slums of Venezuela to learn to play an instrument(n)

programme.desc: Marc-André Hamelin from Canada owes his fame to his musical virtuosity and refined piano techniques. programme.title: Mozart
programme.desc: None other than Ludwig van Beethoven played Mozart's Piano Concerto No. 25 at his first Vienna solo performance. A special homage for a special concert. Wolfgang Amadeus Mozart completed this piece on December 4, 1786 and performed it for the first time on the day after(n)

programme.title: Beethoven
programme.desc: Ta-ta-ta-taa': quite possibly the most famous opening sequence, to one of the most famous symphonies ever written. It has become impossible to think of concert halls today without Beethoven's 'Fifth', but for a symphony this popular it had a rather disastrous opening night(n)

programme.title: Brahms
programme.desc: I will have to admit, this is the first time I smiled to see one of my compositions in print", Johannes Brahms wrote to his publisher when he first laid eyes on his 'Liebeslieder Waltzes'. Originally he wrote the piece for two pianos and vocals.(n)

programme.title: Bruch
programme.desc: Max Bruch's first violin concerto in G minor is one of the most popular violin concertos in the repertoire. Bruch started the composition of this piece in 1857 and on April 24th 1866 it was first performed, with Otto von Köningslow on violin and Bruch himself in charge(n)

programme.title: Liszt
programme.desc: This work forms part of Franz Liszt's 'Années de pèlerinage', a musical journey accompanying the composer's travels with his beloved Marie d'Agoult. Where the first set focused on describing natural scenery, the pieces in this second set describe the artworks Liszt discovers(n)

programme.title: Schubert
programme.desc: Every year, the closing concert of the Pianoscope Festival is a unique moment, in which all musicians who took part in any of the Festival's concerts and masterclasses come together for a majestic conclusion to the festivities. In this broadcast: Franz Schubert's glorious 'Fantasia in f minor'(n)

programme.title: Four Seasons Of Buenos Aires
programme.desc: Invierno Porteño is part of a four-movement cycle named Las cuatro estaciones porteñas or Four Buenos Aires Seasons which, as the name suggests, is a tribute to the tango of Buenos Aires and also to the baroque composer Antonio Vivaldi(n)

programme.title: Takemitsu
programme.desc: With this concert, Yutaka Sado makes his Philharmonic debut. He will be the first Japanese to conduct the renowned orchestra since Seiji Ozawa several years ago. programme.desc: Junte-se a Riley enquanto ele viaja para Las Vegas para ajudar a voar alto o Cirque du Soleil, e resolver um verdadeiro um problema. No centro do espetáculo está o maior e mais avançado teatro tecnológico do mundo - e está a falhar(n)

programme.title: As Maiores Reparações do Mundo
programme.desc: Segure-se firme e faça o que fizer não olhe para baixo! Durante quase sessenta anos, uma antena de TV antiga, fez parte da paisagem de San Antonio. Agora com o desgaste desse tempo, a antena tem de descer antes que caia. A questão é: como(n)

programme.title: O melhor de: Pesca no Limite
programme.desc: O Capitão Tyler McLaughlin, o jovem da frota de Gloucester, chegou com uma missão - destronar o vencedor da temporada 1, o Capitão Dave Cararro do FV-Tuna.com. Este episódio especial mostrará os altos e baixos da carreira de Tyler durante as últimas cinco temporadas(n)

programme.title: O melhor de: Pesca no Limite
programme.desc: A vida de um pescador comercial de Gloucester não é uma forma fácil de ganhar dinheiro. Estas águas perigosamente infames tanto sustêm a vida como a tiram. É necessária uma tenacidade rara para ganhar a vida a pescar este peixe valioso(n)

programme.title: O melhor de: Pesca no Limite
programme.desc: As condições atmosféricas em Gloucester são imprevisíveis e podem mudar em segundos. Estes pescadores têm de estar preparados para relâmpagos, mares agitados, chuva intensa, vento e ondas de calor. Mas vale tudo a pena quando um atum morde(n)

programme.title: Mayday, Desastres Aéreos
programme.desc: Em rota para Boise, Idaho, o Voo 1713 da Continental Airlines é atrasado na pista em Denver, onde os controladores têm dificuldades em manter as partidas dentro do horário por causa de um nevão. programme.title: Mayday, Desastres Aéreos: Casos Especiais
programme.desc: Alguns desastres aéreos mais letais da história foram causados por simples mal entendidos e foi um minúsculo erro no cockpit que levou a tragédia no Quincy Airport de Illinois. programme.title: Mayday, Desastres Aéreos: Casos Especiais

programme.title: Primal Survivor

programme.desc: Bem no interior dos Himalaias, Hazen Audel está numa demanda de levar uma manada de yaques através de uma zona selvagem proibida para a segurança da antiga cidade fortaleza de Lomanthang. programme.title: Ao Encontro de Plutão

programme.title: Missão: Saturno

programme.title: Africa\u0027s Deadliest
programme.desc: You want to up the odds of success, up the numbers. The more attackers there are the better their chances and the bigger the prey. A single lion cant take on a giraffe, but a pride will pull it down. A wild dog has no chance against a wildebeest, but a pack will rip it apart(n)

programme.title: Africa\u0027s Deadliest
programme.desc: Lions get most of the attention but there are many cats that kill. Their size, camouflage and hunting strategy may vary but they're all deadly(n)

programme.title: Puma: Lion Of The Andes
programme.desc: On the southern tip of South America, across the rugged Patagonia region, is one of the few remaining refuges of the puma. Wildlife filmmaker Hugh Miles follows two years in the life of a female puma and her growing cubs, providing unprecedented coverage of a pumas life in the wild(n)

programme.title: Animal Fight Club
programme.desc: Reveals what happens when the Animal Kingdoms most audacious species fight tooth and claw, and brings you closer than ever before to adrenaline-packed fights from all four corners of the globe. In a heavy-weight showdown, one horn takes on two, as a rhino and a buffalo get brutal on the battlefield(n)

programme.title: Ultimate Animal Countdown
programme.desc: Are you a survivor; capable of coping with crashes, cataclysms, and catastrophes? Even the hardest humans are wimps compared to the toughest creatures on the planet. Were counting down the ultimate top ten survivors in the natural world to find the animal with the most extraordinary endurance(n)

programme.title: Europe\u0027s Last Wilderness

programme.title: Wonderfully Weird

programme.title: Wonderfully Weird
programme.desc: Nature is a scary place... and animals battle daily for survival. It's no wonder they need weapons. We know the big bruisers bring their size, hooves, teeth and horns. But what about the "Little" guy... what does he bring to the fray? Secret weapons(n)

programme.title: The Pack
